<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-illegiblelineknown" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Illegible Lines, Quantity Known</head>
    <p><!--gloss--></p>
    <p><specList>
        <specDesc key="gap"/>
    </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p> 
    
    <p>Where vestiges of lines remain, but they cannot be recognised and their quantity is
        known, they should be placed in a <gi>gap</gi> and given a <att>reason</att>
        with a value of "illegible".</p>
    
    <cit>
        <quote>[- - - - - -]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>VIII.5</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="3" unit="line"/>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london" corresp="http://insaph.kcl.ac.uk/iaph2007/iAph080404.html">
        <gap reason="illegible" extent="2" unit="line"/>
    </egXML>
    
    <!-- No IRT examples -->
    <!-- No DDBDP examples -->
    
